      "IP returned to work on 9 September 2021 without limitations"
    ],
    "summary": "On 27 August 2021 at approximately 1400 hours, an injury occurred on Mississippi Canyon (MC) 807 B (Olympus) platform during hurricane evacuation procedures. The Injured Person (IP) sustained a laceration to the left thumb while cutting a section of rope. The IP was wearing gloves but they were not cut-resistant gloves. The IP was using an approved alternative cutting device and followed Shell's policy for the use of cutting devices when the injury occurred. The IP received treatment at an onshore medical facility and fully recovered.",
